        <item>
            <title>政府認可本地研發 CabCab 智能咪錶　第二季支援電子支付</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2024/01/31/cabcab/life-tech/epayment/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=cabcab</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2024/01/31/cabcab/life-tech/epayment/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Wed, 31 Jan 2024 08:48:05 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[智慧城市]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[電子支付]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[CabCab]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[CabCab 智能咪錶]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[智能咪錶]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[的士]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1217826</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>本地的士管理營運商 Mobile Shop 旗下品牌 CabCab 聯同汽車科技研發中心（APAS）宣佈推出獲政府運輸署認可的智能的士咪錶「CabCab」，首階段將於 100 架市區及新界的士施行，預計第 3 季有 1,000 架的士配備智能咪錶。CabCab 表示，支付系統產生的手續費將會由乘客負擔。</p><p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218017" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0393-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0393-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0393.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲CabCab 智能咪錶</p><p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218018" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0270-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0270-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0270.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲CabCab 智能咪錶</p><p>CabCab 董事總經理兼香港無線電的士聯誼會主席黃羽庭表示，CabCab 與傳統的士咪錶不同之處是其提供更多電子化功能，能夠提升司機服務效率及質素。與此同時，開關後香港有很多遊客，部分來自中國的遊客已習慣使用電子錢包支付，加上外國遊客不一定有足夠港幣，電子支付能夠幫助這類遊客。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218000" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0265-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0265-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0265.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p>黃羽庭又指，CabCab 運作初期不會收取司機手續費，另外亦會提供優惠吸引司機安裝智能咪錶。其表示支付系統產生的手續費將會由乘客負擔，不過亦會向乘客提供回饋。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1217995" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0214-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0214-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0214.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲CabCab 董事總經理兼香港無線電的士聯誼會主席黃羽庭</p><p>CabCab 首席執行長許健生表示，CabCab 是本地第一個自主研發並獲得政府認可的智能的士咪錶，預計今年第二季可支援多種支付方式，如八達通、支付寶、銀聯等。首批智能咪錶將會安裝於 100 架比亞迪的士上，其後會逐步替換其他的士上的舊款咪錶。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218001" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0264-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0264-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0264.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲比亞迪的士</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1217997" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0235-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0235-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0235.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲CabCab 首席執行長許健生</p><p>汽車科技研發中心（APAS）行政總裁張梓昌表示，CabCab 可以收集大數據，分析並反饋資料予的士司機，未來將加入車聯網技術，新增 Call 台、定位系統等服務，目標於今年第 3 季度於 1000 架的士上使用。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1217999" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0262-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0262-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0262.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲汽車科技研發中心（APAS）行政總裁張梓昌</p><p>航運交通界立法會議員易志明現場示範了數種電子支付方式。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218004" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0329-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0329-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0329.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><h2>信用卡支付</h2><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218003" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0299-694x390.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0299-694x390.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0299.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218002" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0303-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0303-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0303.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><h2>八達通支付</h2><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218005" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0333-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0333-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0333.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218007" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0340-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0340-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0340.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><h2>PayMe / AliPay</h2><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218008" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0361-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0361-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0361.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218012" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0364-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0364-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0364.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲PayMe</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218013" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0372-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0372-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0372.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲AliPay</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218010" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0365-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0365-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0365.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1218009" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0366-694x521.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="521" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0366-694x521.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/img_0366.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><br /><b>相關文章:</b><blockquote><li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/01/11/octopus-taxi-add-qr-code/life-tech/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">八達通開放的士支付網絡　加入銀聯和支付寶等二維碼選項</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2023/12/21/taxi-3/life-tech/smartcity/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">的士業界指政府承諾修例規管網約車     「感受到政府決心」</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2023/12/03/uber-london-black-cab/life-tech/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">倫敦 Uber 終於可以叫「黑的」　的士司機工會提出反對</a></li>&nbsp;</blockquote><br /><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/01/31/cabcab/life-tech/epayment/">政府認可本地研發 CabCab 智能咪錶　第二季支援電子支付</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
